                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18280110-203-off1064 t18280110-203-crimeloc1067"></join>. I saw the prisoner in his shop on the 2d of January, and saw him take something from the counter, and put into his hat; he stood about ten minutes longer, and was then going out - I said I wanted to speak to him, and went with him to a public-house; I accused him of having something which did not belong to him - he denied it - I said it was in his hat, and desired him to take his hat off, which he refused to do; I took off his hat, and found in it this black waistcoat: I then took an officer, and went to his lodgings, where we found this duplicate of the other property.</p>
